English and Bough begin their journey with farcical side jumps: disguised as waiters, they set fire to a flashy French restaurant. They create chaos while hiding aboard Volta's luxury yacht; and English unleashes the sheer anarchy as he tries to use a VR headset to make himself known in Volta's house.
All the stops are really pulled out before the last sequence, but even so gracious and noisy it is so there is a lot that reminds of children's TV with the whole thing.
Pretty mediocre, all of it.
